    {
      "start": 0.96,
      "end": 20.93,
      "text": "Killing two birds with one stone"
    },
    {
      "start": 20.93,
      "end": 25.03,
      "text": "영화 감상과 영어 공부를 동시에 Screen English Time"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.03,
      "end": 31.93,
      "text": "9월에 함께하고 있는 영화는 음악 영화 어벤져스가 완성한 역대급 뮤직 프로젝트"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.93,
      "end": 32.93,
      "text": "CODA"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.93,
      "end": 33.73,
      "text": "입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.51,
      "end": 35.81,
      "text": "와우, 어서 오세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.81,
      "end": 39.17,
      "text": "Hello, good morning to Laura and everyone, GM Piers."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.29,
      "end": 46.17,
      "text": "Yeah, I just explained like 음악 영화 어벤져스가 완성한 뮤직 프로젝트라고"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.17,
      "end": 50.95,
      "text": "말씀을 드렸는데 특히나 이 라라랜드 영화 보셨나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.37,
      "end": 51.91,
      "text": "Yeah, of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.45,
      "end": 53.33,
      "text": "라라랜드."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.35,
      "end": 56.45,
      "text": "아, 라라랜드. 라라랜드가 아니라 라라랜드."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.03,
      "end": 57.75,
      "text": "로라랜드."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.91,
      "end": 59.25,
      "text": "아, 어울리는데요."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.57,
      "end": 60.51,
      "text": "I like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.57,
      "end": 61.19,
      "text": "You like it."
    },
    {
      "start": 61.29,
      "end": 63.41,
      "text": "Yeah, oh, 로라랜드 괜찮네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.41,
      "end": 70.45,
      "text": "라라랜드의 음악 감독이었던 마리우스 드브리스의 손길을 거친 영화라고 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.55,
      "end": 71.71,
      "text": "Yes, 마리우스 드브리스."
    },
    {
      "start": 71.95,
      "end": 75.97,
      "text": "Yeah, 특히 저는 I still remember the oeste of la-la-land."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.25,
      "end": 76.93,
      "text": "What was it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.09,
      "end": 78.89,
      "text": "Um, city of stars."
    },
    {
      "start": 78.97,
      "end": 80.05,
      "text": "City of stars."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.35,
      "end": 83.01,
      "text": "Are you shining just for me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.19,
      "end": 84.35,
      "text": "Yes, you are."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.19,
      "end": 86.01,
      "text": "계속 하시는 거예요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.41,
      "end": 86.93,
      "text": "계속해 볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.09,
      "end": 88.63,
      "text": "City of stars."
    },
    {
      "start": 88.83,
      "end": 89.55,
      "text": "Boo-da-boo-boo."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.73,
      "end": 92.33,
      "text": "There's so much that I can't see."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.33,
      "end": 94.19,
      "text": "Oh, lovely."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.61,
      "end": 96.95,
      "text": "Oh, 이 반응이 계속 달라지고 계세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.01,
      "end": 97.65,
      "text": "Dun-dun-dun."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.99,
      "end": 99.47,
      "text": "Let's go to a jazz club."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.67,
      "end": 101.71,
      "text": "Jazz club 가야 될 것 같은 아침입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.75,
      "end": 103.69,
      "text": "Have some anju with singing."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.73,
      "end": 104.39,
      "text": "Good idea."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.85,
      "end": 111.55,
      "text": "아무튼 이 마리우스 드브리스라는 영화 감독에 대해서 좀 설명을 듣고 싶은데요."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.55,
      "end": 118.75,
      "text": "Yeah, so he's from the UK, born in 1961, and he's a big English music producer and composer."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.09,
      "end": 124.31,
      "text": "He's won a lot of awards, a Grammy Award, two BAFTA Awards."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.31,
      "end": 136.59,
      "text": "He also has worked on other movies, La La Land, Moulin Rouge, in 2001, and Romeo and Juliet back in 1996."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.99,
      "end": 137.25,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.25,
      "end": 139.81,
      "text": "And I was looking up some of the singers he's worked with."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.81,
      "end": 152.69,
      "text": "He has written, arranged, and produced for many famous singers, including Madonna, David Bowie, David Gray, U2, Josh Groban, and many others."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.69,
      "end": 154.91,
      "text": "So he's a big-time music producer."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.15,
      "end": 155.57,
      "text": "진짜."
    },
    {
      "start": 156.01,
      "end": 157.31,
      "text": "다 들리셨죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.69,
      "end": 163.93,
      "text": "우리의 귀에도 너무나도 익숙한 그만큼 유명한 가수들과 함께 작업을 한 어마어마한 분이네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.15,
      "end": 169.89,
      "text": "특히 이 라라랜드 영화에서는 이분이 played a role of casting director?"
    },
    {
      "start": 170.37,
      "end": 170.83,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.91,
      "end": 171.23,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.33,
      "end": 173.39,
      "text": "He actually had a part in the movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.47,
      "end": 174.71,
      "text": "So we can see his face."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.83,
      "end": 175.19,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.49,
      "end": 177.53,
      "text": "Oh, 전 기억이 지금 안 나고 있는 상황인데."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.93,
      "end": 181.73,
      "text": "If I watch the movie again, 이 부분을 한번 다시 자세히 봐야 되겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.73,
      "end": 182.61,
      "text": "Watch it again."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.69,
      "end": 183.01,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.27,
      "end": 187.51,
      "text": "아무튼 이 코다에서 이분의 손길이 있었다라는 거 기억해 주시고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 187.87,
      "end": 189.27,
      "text": "오늘 장면 먼저 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.27,
      "end": 192.33,
      "text": "When we were little, I used to see you guys in town."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.79,
      "end": 193.03,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 193.65,
      "end": 194.73,
      "text": "We were hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 195.29,
      "end": 198.38,
      "text": "There's this one time, I think it was like third grade."
    },
    {
      "start": 199.14,
      "end": 202.14,
      "text": "You were at the Seapwork Grill and you were ordering for your parents."
    },
    {
      "start": 202.96,
      "end": 205.62,
      "text": "And you were talking to the waiter like a total baller."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.61,
      "end": 207.91,
      "text": "And then you ordered two beers."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.87,
      "end": 210.01,
      "text": "I thought it was so cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.49,
      "end": 210.79,
      "text": "Really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.45,
      "end": 211.87,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.87,
      "end": 214.95,
      "text": "My parents wouldn't even let me ride the bus by myself."
    },
    {
      "start": 216.36,
      "end": 217.92,
      "text": "They're hitting it off."
    },
    {
      "start": 218.08,
      "end": 218.4,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 218.52,
      "end": 221.26,
      "text": "정말 잘 어울리는 한 쌍입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.76,
      "end": 222.06,
      "text": "그죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 222.06,
      "end": 227.58,
      "text": "그리고 제가 생각하기에는 they must have lived in that town for a long time."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.58,
      "end": 229.26,
      "text": "They're already neighbors."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.76,
      "end": 229.96,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 230.04,
      "end": 232.06,
      "text": "They're talking about their childhood."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.24,
      "end": 234.68,
      "text": "They grew up in this small fishing town."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.78,
      "end": 235.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 235.16,
      "end": 238.16,
      "text": "And they have memories of each other, each other's families."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.16,
      "end": 243.46,
      "text": "어렸을 때부터 서로의 가족들을 이렇게 관찰을 하면서 보낼 수가 있는 상황이었나 봐요."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.98,
      "end": 247.14,
      "text": "근데 제 생각에는 Miles가요, had a thing for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 247.58,
      "end": 247.9,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.04,
      "end": 248.76,
      "text": "Yeah, something."
    },
    {
      "start": 249.0,
      "end": 250.08,
      "text": "He had something."
    },
    {
      "start": 250.22,
      "end": 251.28,
      "text": "Yeah, you told me."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.78,
      "end": 253.28,
      "text": "He thought she was cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.4,
      "end": 253.7,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.82,
      "end": 254.94,
      "text": "He admired her."
    },
    {
      "start": 255.04,
      "end": 256.98,
      "text": "그리고 좋아한 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.36,
      "end": 257.84,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.38,
      "end": 259.18,
      "text": "옛날부터."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.32,
      "end": 259.68,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.02,
      "end": 261.98,
      "text": "Wow, that girl is different."
    },
    {
      "start": 262.1,
      "end": 262.9,
      "text": "장난 아니네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.0,
      "end": 263.84,
      "text": "She is special."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.84,
      "end": 267.32,
      "text": "자, 어떤 단어들, 표현들이 있었는지 살펴보겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 267.92,
      "end": 268.8,
      "text": "Hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.0,
      "end": 269.94,
      "text": "Hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 270.28,
      "end": 273.94,
      "text": "놓치기 어려운 이라는 의미로 오늘 맥락에서 들으셨어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 274.14,
      "end": 275.04,
      "text": "It's hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.22,
      "end": 277.4,
      "text": "It's really big, really bright."
    },
    {
      "start": 277.54,
      "end": 280.18,
      "text": "When you're giving directions to someone."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.3,
      "end": 281.26,
      "text": "네, 그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.44,
      "end": 287.5,
      "text": "길, 방향 이런 거 알려줄 때 어떤 건물이 있다라고 하는데 그때 hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 287.76,
      "end": 291.0,
      "text": "놓치기 어려울 정도로 그만큼 잘 뛴다라는 의미가 되겠죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 291.08,
      "end": 292.08,
      "text": "You can't miss it."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.34,
      "end": 292.8,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.74,
      "end": 294.34,
      "text": "Total."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.5,
      "end": 295.48,
      "text": "Oh, I like this one."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.56,
      "end": 295.76,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.76,
      "end": 297.26,
      "text": "Total baller."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.72,
      "end": 299.1,
      "text": "이 표현을 좋아하신대요."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.1,
      "end": 303.92,
      "text": "Well, this just brings back memories from when I was younger in California."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.78,
      "end": 308.58,
      "text": "It's slang, but very common slang for young people."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.26,
      "end": 312.94,
      "text": "Originally from basketball or sports with a ball."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.36,
      "end": 318.16,
      "text": "Like if you're really good at basketball, you could call yourself a baller."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.16,
      "end": 324.04,
      "text": "But now it just means to be cool, awesome, 뭐 짱, baller."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.04,
      "end": 332.2,
      "text": "네, baller이라고 하면 농구 선수라든지 어쨌든 공에 관련된 플레이를 잘하는 사람에 대해서 baller이라고 할 것 같잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.2,
      "end": 342.66,
      "text": "물론 그럴 때도 쓸 수 있지만 좀 전에 설명을 들으신 것처럼 짱, 멋진 사람을 나타낼 때 baller이라는 표현을 쓴다고 하셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.9,
      "end": 348.82,
      "text": "그리고 그 앞에 total이라는 게 붙어 있으니까 total baller 하면 아주 멋진 사람."
    },
    {
      "start": 348.82,
      "end": 353.68,
      "text": "짱, 짱, 짱, 맨 되겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.0,
      "end": 354.52,
      "text": "짱, 짱, 맨."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.66,
      "end": 355.52,
      "text": "I like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.02,
      "end": 356.54,
      "text": "A good one."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.7,
      "end": 356.82,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.64,
      "end": 359.08,
      "text": "I thought it was so cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.42,
      "end": 361.16,
      "text": "I thought it was so cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.6,
      "end": 364.16,
      "text": "나는 정말 멋지다고 생각했어."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.38,
      "end": 365.28,
      "text": "라는 문장입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.96,
      "end": 367.54,
      "text": "네, 이 장면 다시 한번 들어볼게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.54,
      "end": 370.58,
      "text": "When we were little, I used to see you guys in town."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.02,
      "end": 371.28,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 372.08,
      "end": 372.96,
      "text": "We were hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.52,
      "end": 380.37,
      "text": "There was this one time, I think it was like third grade, you were at the Seaport Grill and you were ordering for your parents."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.19,
      "end": 383.85,
      "text": "And you were talking to the waiter like a total baller."
    },
    {
      "start": 384.85,
